      <li>Each round pays out <strong>90.25%</strong> of the ticket pool as prizes (90.25 USDT on the 1 USDT battlefield), and <strong>56% of participants</strong> walk away with USDT.</li>
      <li>A further <strong>5%</strong> of the pool feeds the Epoch grand prize pool, and <strong>4.75%</strong> is the platform reserve (a portion of which feeds the Growth Incentive Pool, flowing back to users who keep growing in <a href="/en/level/">Level</a>).</li>
      <li>The Sovereign and the leaders also take their places on this round's Endorsement Board, earning the right to contend for the Epoch grand prize and the Grand Chieftain's throne.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The Fallen: The Spirit's Choice</h2>
    <p>
      In NU World, falling is not the end. The Battle Souls of the 44 Fallen become <strong>Spirits</strong>,
      and each Spirit must make one <strong>irreversible</strong> choice (pick one of two):
    </p>
    <h3>🔥 Forge the Soul</h3>
    <p>
      Smelt your Spirit into <strong>Mind Crystals</strong> — NU World's in-ecosystem resource, usable for
      NFT enhancement, character evolution, and special seasonal gameplay. Note: Mind Crystals cannot be
      converted back into USDT.
    </p>
    <h3>🗳️ Endorse a Leader</h3>
    <p>
      Cast your one and only vote (weight 1.0) for any leader on this round's Endorsement Board. The vote
      is recorded on-chain and, once cast, is <strong>final — it cannot be changed or withdrawn</strong>.
      Your vote accumulates toward the Grand Chieftain's coronation at the Epoch's finale — and Spirits
      who take part in the endorsement stand a chance to share in the Epoch grand prize (see below).
    </p>

    <h2>The Epoch Grand Prize and the Grand Chieftain's Coronation</h2>
    <p>
      Every 11 rounds form an <strong>Epoch</strong>. 5% of each round's ticket pool feeds the grand prize
      pool (5 USDT per round on the 1 USDT battlefield), accumulating to <strong>55 USDT</strong> by the
      Epoch's end, settled as follows:
    </p>
    <div class="table-wrap"><table>
      <thead><tr><th>Recipients</th><th>Share</th><th>Amount</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Leaders on the Endorsement Board</td><td>90%</td><td>49.5 USDT</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Endorsement voters (roughly 1% of Spirits drawn at random as the lucky winners)</td><td>10%</td><td>5.5 USDT</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table></div>
    <p>
      At the Epoch's finale, the leader with the most endorsement votes is crowned
      <strong>Grand Chieftain</strong>, their name inscribed forever in the chronicles of NU World.
    </p>

    <h2>Claims, Refunds, and Common Operations</h2>
    <h3>Claiming your prize</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>After the draw, go to "My Holdings" and hit Claim on each Battle Soul to reveal its result and collect the prize.</li>
      <li>Prizes land in your wallet instantly — <strong>no lock-up, no delayed payouts</strong>. If an on-chain transfer temporarily fails, the amount is credited to your pending balance and can be claimed again at any time.</li>
      <li>Claim rights belong to the NFT's <strong>current holder</strong>; each Battle Soul can only be claimed once.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Refunds</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>If a round fails to sell all 100 tickets within 24 hours, it automatically enters the cancellation process.</li>
      <li>Buyers can reclaim the full ticket price, down to the last cent; the Battle Soul NFT becomes a commemorative "empty chest".</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Fairness</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Randomness comes from Chainlink VRF v2.5</strong>: the random seed's generation and cryptographic proof live entirely on-chain, verifiable by anyone — the platform cannot foresee or manipulate the draw's outcome.</li>
      <li><strong>Distribution ratios are hard-coded into the smart contract</strong>: prize tiers, grand prize pool contributions, and the platform reserve ratio are all locked in the contract — once a round opens, no one can change them.</li>
      <li><strong>One ticket per address</strong>: guaranteeing every round is a battlefield of 100 real participants.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <h3>Q: What is the relationship between Arena and NU World?</h3>
    <p>
      Arena is the platform's competitive division (the parent), containing multiple independent game
      worlds; NU World is the first world to officially open. Future worlds will carry their own themes
      and economic parameters, each with a corresponding world guide.
    </p>
    <h3>Q: What do I need before I can join a battle?</h3>
    <p>A BSC wallet, enough USDT to cover your chosen battlefield's ticket price (light battlefields start at 1 USDT), a small amount of BNB for gas, and a LevelUp Land account with your wallet linked.</p>
    <h3>Q: I bought a ticket but the draw hasn't happened — what now?</h3>
    <p>The draw waits until all 100 tickets in the round are sold. If the round doesn't sell out within 24 hours, it is cancelled and you can claim a full refund.</p>
    <h3>Q: Can Battle Soul NFTs be transferred?</h3>
    <p>Yes. A Battle Soul is a standard on-chain NFT and can be transferred before its prize is claimed; claim rights move with the NFT to its current holder.</p>
    <h3>Q: I endorsed the wrong leader — can I change my vote?</h3>
    <p>No. Endorsement is an irreversible on-chain action — choose the leader you want to champion carefully before voting.</p>
    <h3>Q: Can Mind Crystals be converted back into USDT?</h3>
    <p>No. Mind Crystals are an in-ecosystem resource, used only for enhancement, evolution, and special gameplay within NU World.</p>
    <h3>Q: Where do the platform's retained funds go?</h3>
    <p>
      Of the 4.75% platform reserve from each round's pool (4.75 USDT on the 1 USDT battlefield), a portion
      feeds the Growth Incentive Pool, rewarding users who keep growing along the
      <a href="/en/level/">Level Voyage Map</a> — the heat of the Arena ultimately flows back to those who
      persist in growing.
    </p>

    <p class="page-note">
      A note on responsible play: Arena is on-chain competitive gameplay, and each round's outcome is
      decided by verifiable randomness. Play within your means, and enjoy the game and its story for
      their own sake.
    </p>
